Devils Thumb () is a mountain located near Mossman within the Daintree National Park, Far North Queensland, Australia. Devils Thumb rises  above sea level.
The Manjal Jamalji trail is a difficult 10.6-kilometre return trail to the peak which takes approximately eight hours.
